How ADW Live Rating works

ADW Live Rating is a ranking system for agility teams (handler + dog) based on results from international competitions. It uses the OpenSkill (Plackett-Luce) statistical model, a modern alternative to Elo or Glicko — unlike those systems, it can work with full run rankings (not just win/loss) and is designed for multi-participant competitions.

Core concept

Each team has two internal parameters:

  • mu (μ) — estimate of the team's true skill. Higher = better.
  • sigma (σ) — uncertainty measure. New teams have high sigma; it decreases with more runs.

After each run, the model compares the actual result with the expected ranking and adjusts mu and sigma for all participants.

Sigma decay

After each processed run, sigma is multiplied by a factor of 0.99. This means confidence in the team's rating grows with more data. Minimum sigma is 1.5.

Public rating calculation

rating_base = 1000 + 40 × (μ − 1.0 × σ)
rating = rating_base × quality_factor

Podium boost (quality factor)

The public rating is adjusted based on the quality of a team's results:

quality_factor = 0.85 + 0.20 × clamp(top3% / 50)

Quality factor ranges from 0.85 (no top-3 finishes) to 1.05 (frequent podium placements). Teams that consistently finish in the top 3 receive a significant bonus, while teams without podium results have their rating reduced.

Competition weighting (tier system)

Competitions are divided into two tiers:

  • Major (tier 1) — AWC, EO, JOAWC/SOAWC — runs carry 1.2× weight
  • Open (tier 2) — other international competitions — standard 1.0× weight

Higher weight for Major events means results from these prestigious competitions have a greater impact on rating changes.

Skill tiers

TierConditionColor
EliteTop 2% in categorygold
ChampionTop 10%purple
ExpertTop 30%blue
CompetitorEveryone elsegreen

Few runs status

A team with σ ≥ 7.8 is marked as FEW RUNS — this means the system doesn't yet have enough data for a reliable estimate. The rating will stabilize with more runs.

Live window and minimum runs

  • Only runs from the last 913 days (~2.5 years) from the latest competition in the dataset are counted.
  • A minimum of 5 runs within this window is required to appear in the rankings.
  • Minimum participants per run for it to count: 6

System parameters

ParameterValueDescription
LIVE_WINDOW_DAYS913Time window for counting runs
MIN_RUNS5Minimum runs to appear in rankings
SIGMA_DECAY0.99Uncertainty reduction factor per run
SIGMA_MIN1.5Minimum sigma (floor)
PROV_THRESHOLD7.8Sigma threshold for provisional status
DISPLAY_BASE1000Public rating base
DISPLAY_SCALE40Scaling factor
MAJOR_WEIGHT1.2Major event weight multiplier
PODIUM_BASE0.85Minimum quality factor
PODIUM_RANGE0.2Quality factor range
MIN_FIELD_SIZE6Minimum participants per run
